05/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The media campaign for the collection of illegal weapons in Macedonia will start on Wednesday (6 August), the sponsor of the UNDP project said Tuesday. The campaign will continue until 1 November, when the process of voluntary surrender of illegal arms will take place. Currently, citizens can apply for the registration of unreported personal weapons that they possess.
In other news Tuesday, the Macedonian Defence Ministry adopted a plan to transfer army dodgers to the army's reserve. Men between the ages of 27 and 30 who evaded military service, but received amnesty, will have six months to register. (MIA, A1 TV - 04/08/03)
